CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 18, 1961, pg. 19 reads: Swing Your Partner - Loendi Club took on the air of an old-fashioned barn recently when the Loendi Ladies Auxlliary [sic] sponsored a square dance in club's parlors..."Coming Through the Rye," might well have been the cry as the couples dance through a formed arch, as shown in the last photograph [second].-Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Women making arch, and chain of women, including one on left wearing plaid dress, and men, dancing through it, in Loendi Club, during square dance sponsored by the Loendi Ladies Auxiliary
